It is undeniable that the Civil Rights movement has completely changed the course of left-wing discourse in the United States. Class struggle, anti-capitalism and anti-globalization have all been pushed to the periphery with greater favor being placed on continuing the legacy of anti-racism, countermajoritarianism and minoritarianism. 

After half a century since the end of the Civil Rights movement, how do you feel about the course of race relations in the United States? Have they improved, worsened or perhaps stalemated? From the current trends, where do you see race relations going? What is the legacy of the Civil Rights movement?
